Index of All Objects

ADOM Level Objects Objects Reference (For v7.2)


This documentation applies to v7.2 devices or ADOM, latest release (build 1681).

adom/options (object)

Supported methods: get, set, update

Object URL:
Table object/pm/config/global/obj/adom/options
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/adom/options
Attribute ListDescriptions
assign_excludedoption
"disable"
"enable"
assign_namestring
specify_assign_pkg_listoption
"disable"
"enable"

 

antivirus/profile (table)

Configure AntiVirus profiles.

Supported methods: get (table), get (object), add, set, update, delete, clone

Object URL:
Table/pm/config/global/obj/antivirus/profile
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/antivirus/profile
Object/pm/config/global/obj/antivirus/profile/<profile_name>
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/antivirus/profile/<profile_name>
Attribute ListDescriptions
analytics-accept-filetypedatasource, refer to dlp filepattern (maximum 1)
Only submit files matching this DLP file-pattern to FortiSandbox (post-transfer scan only).
analytics-dboption
Enable/disable using the FortiSandbox signature database to supplement the AV signature databases.
"disable"Use only the standard AV signature databases.
"enable"Also use the FortiSandbox signature database.
analytics-ignore-filetypedatasource, refer to dlp filepattern (maximum 1)
Do not submit files matching this DLP file-pattern to FortiSandbox (post-transfer scan only).
av-block-logoption
Enable/disable logging for AntiVirus file blocking.
"disable"Disable setting.
"enable"Enable setting.
av-virus-logoption
Enable/disable AntiVirus logging.
"disable"Disable setting.
"enable"Enable setting.
cifsobject
commentstring
Comment.
content-disarmobject
ems-threat-feedoption
Enable/disable use of EMS threat feed when performing AntiVirus scan. Analyzes files including the content of archives.
"disable"Disable use of EMS threat feed when performing AntiVirus scan.
"enable"Enable use of EMS threat feed when performing AntiVirus scan.
extended-logoption
Enable/disable extended logging for antivirus.
"disable"Disable setting.
"enable"Enable setting.
external-blocklistdatasource, refer to system external-resource
One or more external malware block lists.
external-blocklist-enable-alloption
Enable/disable all external blocklists.
"disable"Use configured external blocklists.
"enable"Enable all external blocklists.
feature-setoption
Flow/proxy feature set.
"proxy"Proxy feature set.
"flow"Flow feature set.
fortindr-error-actionoption
Action to take if FortiNDR encounters an error.
"log-only"Log FortiNDR error, but allow the file.
"block"Block the file on FortiNDR error.
"ignore"Do nothing on FortiNDR error.
fortindr-timeout-actionoption
Action to take if FortiNDR encounters a scan timeout.
"log-only"Log FortiNDR scan timeout, but allow the file.
"block"Block the file on FortiNDR scan timeout.
"ignore"Do nothing on FortiNDR scan timeout.
fortisandbox-error-actionoption
Action to take if FortiSandbox inline scan encounters an error.
"log-only"Log FortiSandbox inline scan error, but allow the file.
"block"Block the file on FortiSandbox inline scan error.
"ignore"Do nothing on FortiSandbox inline scan error.
fortisandbox-max-uploadunsigned int32
Maximum size of files that can be uploaded to FortiSandbox.
fortisandbox-modeoption
FortiSandbox scan modes.
"inline"FortiSandbox inline scan.
"analytics-suspicious"FortiSandbox post-transfer scan: submit supported files if heuristics or other methods determine they are suspicious.
"analytics-everything"FortiSandbox post-transfer scan: submit supported files and known infected files.
fortisandbox-timeout-actionoption
Action to take if FortiSandbox inline scan encounters a scan timeout.
"log-only"Log FortiSandbox inline scan timeout, but allow the file.
"block"Block the file on FortiSandbox inline scan timeout.
"ignore"Do nothing on FortiSandbox inline scan timeout.
ftpobject
httpobject
imapobject
mapiobject
mobile-malware-dboption
Enable/disable using the mobile malware signature database.
"disable"Do not use the mobile malware signature database.
"enable"Also use the mobile malware signature database.
nac-quarobject
namestring, master key
Profile name.
nntpobject
outbreak-prevention-archive-scanoption
Enable/disable outbreak-prevention archive scanning.
"disable"Analyze files as sent, not the content of archives.
"enable"Analyze files including the content of archives.
pop3object
replacemsg-groupdatasource, refer to system replacemsg-group (maximum 1)
Replacement message group customized for this profile.
scan-modeoption
Configure scan mode (default or legacy).
"legacy"Scan archive files only after the entire file is received.
"default"On the fly decompression and scanning of certain archive files.
smtpobject
sshobject

 

antivirus/profile/cifs (object)

Configure CIFS AntiVirus options.

Supported methods: get, set, update

Object URL:
Table object/pm/config/global/obj/antivirus/profile/<profile_name>/cifs
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/antivirus/profile/<profile_name>/cifs
Attribute ListDescriptions
archive-blockflags
Select the archive types to block.
"encrypted"Block encrypted archives.
"corrupted"Block corrupted archives.
"multipart"Block multipart archives.
"nested"Block nested archives that exceed uncompressed nest limit.
"mailbomb"Block mail bomb archives.
"unhandled"Block archives that FortiOS cannot open.
"partiallycorrupted"Block partially corrupted archives.
"timeout"Block scan timeout.
archive-logflags
Select the archive types to log.
"encrypted"Log encrypted archives.
"corrupted"Log corrupted archives.
"multipart"Log multipart archives.
"nested"Log nested archives that exceed uncompressed nest limit.
"mailbomb"Log mail bomb archives.
"unhandled"Log archives that FortiOS cannot open.
"partiallycorrupted"Log partially corrupted archives.
"timeout"Log scan timeout.
av-scanoption
Enable AntiVirus scan service.
"disable"Disable.
"monitor"Log the virus infected files.
"block"Block the virus infected files.
emulatoroption
Enable/disable the virus emulator.
"disable"Disable the virus emulator.
"enable"Enable the virus emulator.
external-blocklistoption
Enable external-blocklist. Analyzes files including the content of archives.
"disable"Disable.
"monitor"Log the matched files.
"block"Block the matched files.
fortindroption
Enable scanning of files by FortiNDR.
"disable"Disable.
"block"Block the FortiNDR detected infections.
"monitor"Log the FortiNDR detected infections.
fortisandboxoption
Enable scanning of files by FortiSandbox.
"disable"Disable.
"block"Block the FortiSandbox detected infections.
"monitor"Log the FortiSandbox detected infections.
outbreak-preventionoption
Enable virus outbreak prevention service.
"disable"Disable.
"block"Block the matched files.
"monitor"Log the matched files.
quarantineoption
Enable/disable quarantine for infected files.
"disable"Disable quarantine for infected files.
"enable"Enable quarantine for infected files.

 

antivirus/profile/content-disarm (object)

AV Content Disarm and Reconstruction settings.

Supported methods: get, set, update

Object URL:
Table object/pm/config/global/obj/antivirus/profile/<profile_name>/content-disarm
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/antivirus/profile/<profile_name>/content-disarm
Attribute ListDescriptions
cover-pageoption
Enable/disable inserting a cover page into the disarmed document.
"disable"Disable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
"enable"Enable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
detect-onlyoption
Enable/disable only detect disarmable files, do not alter content.
"disable"Disable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
"enable"Enable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
error-actionoption
Action to be taken if CDR engine encounters an unrecoverable error.
"block"Block file on CDR error.
"log-only"Log CDR error, but allow file.
"ignore"Do nothing on CDR error.
office-actionoption
Enable/disable stripping of PowerPoint action events in Microsoft Office documents.
"disable"Disable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
"enable"Enable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
office-ddeoption
Enable/disable stripping of Dynamic Data Exchange events in Microsoft Office documents.
"disable"Disable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
"enable"Enable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
office-embedoption
Enable/disable stripping of embedded objects in Microsoft Office documents.
"disable"Disable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
"enable"Enable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
office-hylinkoption
Enable/disable stripping of hyperlinks in Microsoft Office documents.
"disable"Disable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
"enable"Enable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
office-linkedoption
Enable/disable stripping of linked objects in Microsoft Office documents.
"disable"Disable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
"enable"Enable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
office-macrooption
Enable/disable stripping of macros in Microsoft Office documents.
"disable"Disable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
"enable"Enable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
original-file-destinationoption
Destination to send original file if active content is removed.
"fortisandbox"Send original file to configured FortiSandbox.
"quarantine"Send original file to quarantine.
"discard"Original file will be discarded after content disarm.
pdf-act-formoption
Enable/disable stripping of PDF document actions that submit data to other targets.
"disable"Disable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
"enable"Enable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
pdf-act-gotoroption
Enable/disable stripping of PDF document actions that access other PDF documents.
"disable"Disable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
"enable"Enable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
pdf-act-javaoption
Enable/disable stripping of PDF document actions that execute JavaScript code.
"disable"Disable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
"enable"Enable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
pdf-act-launchoption
Enable/disable stripping of PDF document actions that launch other applications.
"disable"Disable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
"enable"Enable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
pdf-act-movieoption
Enable/disable stripping of PDF document actions that play a movie.
"disable"Disable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
"enable"Enable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
pdf-act-soundoption
Enable/disable stripping of PDF document actions that play a sound.
"disable"Disable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
"enable"Enable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
pdf-embedfileoption
Enable/disable stripping of embedded files in PDF documents.
"disable"Disable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
"enable"Enable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
pdf-hyperlinkoption
Enable/disable stripping of hyperlinks from PDF documents.
"disable"Disable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
"enable"Enable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
pdf-javacodeoption
Enable/disable stripping of JavaScript code in PDF documents.
"disable"Disable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.
"enable"Enable this Content Disarm and Reconstruction feature.

"monitor"Log the matched files.
quarantineoption
Enable/disable quarantine for infected files.
"disable"Disable quarantine for infected files.
"enable"Enable quarantine for infected files.
unknown-content-encodingoption
Configure the action the FortiGate unit will take on unknown content-encoding.
"block"Block HTTP session when unknown content-encoding is detected.
"inspect"Inspect HTTP traffic as plain-text with AV scan when unknown content-encoding is detected.
"bypass"Bypass AV scan when unknown content-encoding is detected.

antivirus/profile/nac-quar (object)

Configure AntiVirus quarantine settings.

Supported methods: get, set, update

Object URL:
Table object/pm/config/global/obj/antivirus/profile/<profile_name>/nac-quar
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/antivirus/profile/<profile_name>/nac-quar
Attribute ListDescriptions
expirystring
Duration of quarantine.
infectedoption
Enable/Disable quarantining infected hosts to the banned user list.
"none"Do not quarantine infected hosts.
"quar-src-ip"Quarantine all traffic from the infected hosts source IP.
logoption
Enable/disable AntiVirus quarantine logging.
"disable"Disable AntiVirus quarantine logging.
"enable"Enable AntiVirus quarantine logging.

Object/pm/config/global/obj/dnsfilter/profile/<profile_name>/dns-translation/<dns-translation_id>
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/dnsfilter/profile/<profile_name>/dns-translation/<dns-translation_id>
Attribute ListDescriptions
addr-typeoption
DNS translation type (IPv4 or IPv6).
"ipv4"IPv4 address type.
"ipv6"IPv6 address type.
dstIPv4 address
IPv4 address or subnet on the external network to substitute for the resolved address in DNS query replies. Can be single IP address or subnet on the external network, but number of addresses must equal number of mapped IP addresses in src.
dst6IPv6 address
IPv6 address or subnet on the external network to substitute for the resolved address in DNS query replies. Can be single IP address or subnet on the external network, but number of addresses must equal number of mapped IP addresses in src6.
idsequence, master key
ID.
netmaskIPv4 mask
If src and dst are subnets rather than single IP addresses, enter the netmask for both src and dst.
prefixunsigned int32
If src6 and dst6 are subnets rather than single IP addresses, enter the prefix for both src6 and dst6 (1 - 128, default = 128).
srcIPv4 address
IPv4 address or subnet on the internal network to compare with the resolved address in DNS query replies. If the resolved address matches, the resolved address is substituted with dst.
src6IPv6 address
IPv6 address or subnet on the internal network to compare with the resolved address in DNS query replies. If the resolved address matches, the resolved address is substituted with dst6.
statusoption
Enable/disable this DNS translation entry.
"disable"Disable this DNS translation.
"enable"Enable this DNS translation.

firewall/access-proxy/api-gateway6 (table)

Set IPv6 API Gateway.

Supported methods: get (table), get (object), add, set, update, delete, clone

Object URL:
Table/pm/config/global/obj/firewall/access-proxy/<access-proxy_name>/api-gateway6
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/firewall/access-proxy/<access-proxy_name>/api-gateway6
Object/pm/config/global/obj/firewall/access-proxy/<access-proxy_name>/api-gateway6/<api-gateway6_id>
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/firewall/access-proxy/<access-proxy_name>/api-gateway6/<api-gateway6_id>
Attribute ListDescriptions
applicationstring array
SaaS application controlled by this Access Proxy.
http-cookie-ageunsigned int32
Time in minutes that client web browsers should keep a cookie. Default is 60 minutes. 0 = no time limit.
http-cookie-domainstring
Domain that HTTP cookie persistence should apply to.
http-cookie-domain-from-hostoption
Enable/disable use of HTTP cookie domain from host field in HTTP.
"disable"Disable use of HTTP cookie domain from host field in HTTP (use http-cooke-domain setting).
"enable"Enable use of HTTP cookie domain from host field in HTTP.
http-cookie-generationunsigned int32
Generation of HTTP cookie to be accepted. Changing invalidates all existing cookies.
http-cookie-pathstring
Limit HTTP cookie persistence to the specified path.
http-cookie-shareoption
Control sharing of cookies across API Gateway. Use of same-ip means a cookie from one virtual server can be used by another. Disable stops cookie sharing.
"disable"Only allow HTTP cookie to match this API Gateway.
"same-ip"Allow HTTP cookie to match any API Gateway with same IP.
https-cookie-secureoption
Enable/disable verification that inserted HTTPS cookies are secure.
"disable"Do not mark cookie as secure, allow sharing between an HTTP and HTTPS connection.
"enable"Mark inserted cookie as secure, cookie can only be used for HTTPS a connection.
idsequence, master key
API Gateway ID.
ldb-methodoption
Method used to distribute sessions to real servers.
"static"Distribute to server based on source IP.
"round-robin"Distribute to server based round robin order.
"weighted"Distribute to server based on weight.
"first-alive"Distribute to the first server that is alive.
"http-host"Distribute to server based on host field in HTTP header.
persistenceoption
Configure how to make sure that clients connect to the same server every time they make a request that is part of the same session.
"none"None.
"http-cookie"HTTP cookie.
realserverstable
saml-redirectoption
Enable/disable SAML redirection after successful authentication.
"disable"Do not support redirection after successful SAML authentication.
"enable"Support redirection after successful SAML authentication.
saml-serverdatasource, refer to user saml (maximum 1)
SAML service provider configuration for VIP authentication.
serviceoption
Service.
"http"HTTP.
"https"HTTPS.
"tcp-forwarding"TCP-FORWARDING.
"samlsp"SAML-SP.
"web-portal"VPN-SSL-WEB-PORTAL.
"saas"SAAS.
ssl-algorithmoption
Permitted encryption algorithms for the server side of SSL full mode sessions according to encryption strength.
"high"High encryption. Allow only AES and ChaCha.
"medium"Medium encryption. Allow AES, ChaCha, 3DES, and RC4.
"low"Low encryption. Allow AES, ChaCha, 3DES, RC4, and DES.
ssl-cipher-suitestable
ssl-dh-bitsoption
Number of bits to use in the Diffie-Hellman exchange for RSA encryption of SSL sessions.
"768"768-bit Diffie-Hellman prime.
"1024"1024-bit Diffie-Hellman prime.
"1536"1536-bit Diffie-Hellman prime.
"2048"2048-bit Diffie-Hellman prime.
"3072"3072-bit Diffie-Hellman prime.
"4096"4096-bit Diffie-Hellman prime.
ssl-max-versionoption
Highest SSL/TLS version acceptable from a server.
"tls-1.0"TLS 1.0.
"tls-1.1"TLS 1.1.
"tls-1.2"TLS 1.2.
"tls-1.3"TLS 1.3.
ssl-min-versionoption
Lowest SSL/TLS version acceptable from a server.
"tls-1.0"TLS 1.0.
"tls-1.1"TLS 1.1.
"tls-1.2"TLS 1.2.
"tls-1.3"TLS 1.3.
ssl-renegotiationoption
Enable/disable secure renegotiation to comply with RFC 5746.
"disable"Disable secure renegotiation.
"enable"Enable secure renegotiation.
ssl-vpn-web-portaldatasource, refer to vpn ssl web portal (maximum 1)
SSL-VPN web portal.
url-mapstring
URL pattern to match.
url-map-typeoption
Type of url-map.
"sub-string"Match the pattern if a string contains the sub-string.
"wildcard"Match the pattern with wildcards.
"regex"Match the pattern with a regular expression.
virtual-hostdatasource, refer to firewall access-proxy-virtual-host (maximum 1)
Virtual host.

 

firewall/access-proxy/api-gateway6/realservers (table)

Select the real servers that this Access Proxy will distribute traffic to.

Supported methods: get (table), get (object), add, set, update, delete, clone

Object URL:
Table/pm/config/global/obj/firewall/access-proxy/<access-proxy_name>/api-gateway6/<api-gateway6_id>/realservers
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/firewall/access-proxy/<access-proxy_name>/api-gateway6/<api-gateway6_id>/realservers
Object/pm/config/global/obj/firewall/access-proxy/<access-proxy_name>/api-gateway6/<api-gateway6_id>/realservers/<realservers_id>
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/firewall/access-proxy/<access-proxy_name>/api-gateway6/<api-gateway6_id>/realservers/<realservers_id>
Attribute ListDescriptions
addr-typeoption
Type of address.
"fqdn"Non-wildcard FQDN address object.
"ip"Standard IPv4 address.
addressdatasource, refer to firewall address6, or firewall addrgrp6 (maximum 1)
Address or address group of the real server.
domainstring
Wildcard domain name of the real server.
health-checkoption
Enable to check the responsiveness of the real server before forwarding traffic.
"disable"Disable per server health check.
"enable"Enable per server health check.
health-check-protooption
Protocol of the health check monitor to use when polling to determine server's connectivity status.
"ping"Use PING to test the link with the server.
"http"Use HTTP-GET to test the link with the server.
"tcp-connect"Use a full TCP connection to test the link with the server.
holddown-intervaloption
Enable/disable holddown timer. Server will be considered active and reachable once the holddown period has expired (30 seconds).
"disable"Disable per server holddown.
"enable"Enable per server holddown.
http-hoststring
HTTP server domain name in HTTP header.
idsequence, master key
Real server ID.
ipIPv6 address
IPv6 address of the real server.
mappedportstring array
Port for communicating with the real server.
portunsigned int32
Port for communicating with the real server.
ssh-client-certdatasource, refer to firewall access-proxy-ssh-client-cert (maximum 1)
Set access-proxy SSH client certificate profile.
ssh-host-keydatasource, refer to firewall ssh host-key
One or more server host key.
ssh-host-key-validationoption
Enable/disable SSH real server host key validation.
"disable"Disable SSH real server host key validation.
"enable"Enable SSH real server host key validation.
statusoption
Set the status of the real server to active so that it can accept traffic, or on standby or disabled so no traffic is sent.
"active"Server status active.
"standby"Server status standby.
"disable"Server status disable.
translate-hostoption
Enable/disable translation of hostname/IP from virtual server to real server.
"disable"Disable virtual hostname/IP translation.
"enable"Enable virtual hostname/IP translation.
typeoption
TCP forwarding server type.
"tcp-forwarding"TCP forwarding.
"ssh"SSH.
weightunsigned int32
Weight of the real server. If weighted load balancing is enabled, the server with the highest weight gets more connections.

firewall/ippool (table)

Configure IPv4 IP pools.

Supported methods: get (table), get (object), add, set, update, delete, clone

Object URL:
Table/pm/config/global/obj/firewall/ippool
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/firewall/ippool
Object/pm/config/global/obj/firewall/ippool/<ippool_name>
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/firewall/ippool/<ippool_name>
Attribute ListDescriptions
add-nat64-routeoption
Enable/disable adding NAT64 route.
"disable"Disable adding NAT64 route.
"enable"Enable adding NAT64 route.
arp-intfdatasource, refer to system interface, or dynamic interface (maximum 1) (36 bytes)
Select an interface from available options that will reply to ARP requests. (If blank, any is selected).
arp-replyoption
Enable/disable replying to ARP requests when an IP Pool is added to a policy (default = enable).
"disable"Disable ARP reply.
"enable"Enable ARP reply.
associated-interfacedatasource, refer to system interface, or dynamic interface (maximum 1)
Associated interface name.
block-sizeunsigned int32
Number of addresses in a block (64 - 4096, default = 128).
cgn-block-sizeunsigned int32
Number of ports in a block(64 to 4096 in unit of 64, default = 128).
cgn-client-endipstring
Final client IPv4 address (inclusive) (format xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx, Default: 0.0.0.0).
cgn-client-ipv6shiftunsigned int32
IPv6 shift for fixed-allocation.(default 0)
cgn-client-startipstring
First client IPv4 address (inclusive) (format xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx, Default: 0.0.0.0).
cgn-fixedallocoption
Enable/disable fixed-allocation mode.
"disable"Disable fixed-allocation mode.
"enable"Enable fixed-allocation mode.
cgn-overloadoption
Enable/disable overload mode.
"disable"Disable overload mode.
"enable"Enable overload mode.
cgn-port-endunsigned int32
Ending public port can be allocated.
cgn-port-startunsigned int32
Starting public port can be allocated.
cgn-spaoption
Enable/disable single port allocation mode.
"disable"Disable SPA mode.
"enable"Enable SPA mode.
commentsstring
Comment.
dynamic_mappingtable
endipIPv4 address, support meta variable
Final IPv4 address (inclusive) in the range for the address pool (format xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx, Default: 0.0.0.0).
endportunsigned int32
Final port number (inclusive) in the range for the address pool (Default: 65533).
exclude-ipstring array
Exclude IPs x.x.x.x.
namestring, master key
IP pool name.
nat64option
Enable/disable NAT64.
"disable"Disable DNAT64.
"enable"Enable DNAT64.
num-blocks-per-userunsigned int32
Number of addresses blocks that can be used by a user (1 to 128, default = 8).
pba-timeoutunsigned int32
Port block allocation timeout (seconds).
permit-any-hostoption
Enable/disable full cone NAT.
"disable"Disable full cone NAT.
"enable"Enable full cone NAT.
port-per-userunsigned int32
Number of port for each user (32 - 60416, default = 0, which is auto).
source-endipIPv4 address, support meta variable
Final IPv4 address (inclusive) in the range of the source addresses to be translated (format xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx, Default: 0.0.0.0).
source-startipIPv4 address, support meta variable
First IPv4 address (inclusive) in the range of the source addresses to be translated (format = xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx, default = 0.0.0.0).
startipIPv4 address, support meta variable
First IPv4 address (inclusive) in the range for the address pool (format xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx, Default: 0.0.0.0).
startportunsigned int32
First port number (inclusive) in the range for the address pool (Default: 5117).
subnet-broadcast-in-ippooloption
Enable/disable inclusion of the subnetwork address and broadcast IP address in the NAT64 IP pool.
"disable"Do not include the subnetwork address and broadcast IP address in the NAT64 IP pool.
"enable"Include the subnetwork address and broadcast IP address in the NAT64 IP pool.
typeoption
IP pool type (overload, one-to-one, fixed port range, or port block allocation).
"overload"IP addresses in the IP pool can be shared by clients.
"one-to-one"One to one mapping.
"fixed-port-range"Fixed port range.
"port-block-allocation"Port block allocation.
"cgn-resource-allocation"CGN NAT resource allocation
utilization-alarm-clearunsigned int32
Pool utilization alarm clear threshold (40-100).
utilization-alarm-raiseunsigned int32
Pool utilization alarm raise threshold (50-100).

firewall/ldb-monitor (table)

Configure server load balancing health monitors.

Supported methods: get (table), get (object), add, set, update, delete, clone

Object URL:
Table/pm/config/global/obj/firewall/ldb-monitor
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/firewall/ldb-monitor
Object/pm/config/global/obj/firewall/ldb-monitor/<ldb-monitor_name>
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/firewall/ldb-monitor/<ldb-monitor_name>
Attribute ListDescriptions
dns-match-ipIPv4 address
Response IP expected from DNS server.
dns-protocoloption
Select the protocol used by the DNS health check monitor to check the health of the server (UDP | TCP).
"udp"UDP.
"tcp"TCP.
dns-request-domainstring
Fully qualified domain name to resolve for the DNS probe.
http-getstring
URL used to send a GET request to check the health of an HTTP server.
http-matchstring
String to match the value expected in response to an HTTP-GET request.
http-max-redirectsunsigned int32
The maximum number of HTTP redirects to be allowed (0 - 5, default = 0).
intervalunsigned int32
Time between health checks (5 - 65535 sec, default = 10).
namestring, master key
Monitor name.
portunsigned int32
Service port used to perform the health check. If 0, health check monitor inherits port configured for the server (0 - 65535, default = 0).
retryunsigned int32
Number health check attempts before the server is considered down (1 - 255, default = 3).
src-ipIPv4 address
Source IP for ldb-monitor.
timeoutunsigned int32
Time to wait to receive response to a health check from a server. Reaching the timeout means the health check failed (1 - 255 sec, default = 2).
typeoption
Select the Monitor type used by the health check monitor to check the health of the server (PING | TCP | HTTP | HTTPS | DNS).
"ping"PING health monitor.
"tcp"TCP-connect health monitor.
"http"HTTP-GET health monitor.
"passive-sip"passive-sip health monitor
"https"HTTP-GET health monitor with SSL.
"dns"DNS health monitor.

Supported methods: get (table), get (object), add, set, update, delete, clone

Object URL:

Object/pm/config/global/obj/firewall/multicast-address6/<multicast-address6_name>
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/firewall/multicast-address6/<multicast-address6_name>
Attribute ListDescriptions
colorunsigned int32
Color of icon on the GUI.
commentstring
Comment.
ip6IPv6 prefix
IPv6 address prefix (format: xxxx:xxxx:xxxx:xxxx:xxxx:xxxx:xxxx:xxxx/xxx).
namestring, master key
IPv6 multicast address name.
taggingtable

firewall/profile-protocol-options/cifs (object)

Configure CIFS protocol options.

Supported methods: get, set, update

Object URL:
Table object/pm/config/global/obj/firewall/profile-protocol-options/<profile-protocol-options_name>/cifs
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/firewall/profile-protocol-options/<profile-protocol-options_name>/cifs
Attribute ListDescriptions
domain-controllerdatasource, refer to credential-store domain-controller, or user domain-controller (maximum 1)
Domain for which to decrypt CIFS traffic.
optionsflags
One or more options that can be applied to the session.
"oversize"Block oversized file.
oversize-limitunsigned int32
Maximum in-memory file size that can be scanned (MB).
portsint array
Ports to scan for content (1 - 65535, default = 445).
scan-bzip2option
Enable/disable scanning of BZip2 compressed files.
"disable"Disable setting.
"enable"Enable setting.
server-credential-typeoption
CIFS server credential type.
"none"Credential derivation not set.
"credential-replication"Credential derived using Replication account on Domain Controller.
"credential-keytab"Credential derived using server keytab.
server-keytabtable
statusoption
Enable/disable the active status of scanning for this protocol.
"disable"Disable setting.
"enable"Enable setting.
tcp-window-maximumunsigned int32
Maximum dynamic TCP window size.
tcp-window-minimumunsigned int32
Minimum dynamic TCP window size.
tcp-window-sizeunsigned int32
Set TCP static window size.
tcp-window-typeoption
TCP window type to use for this protocol.
"system"Use system default TCP window size for this protocol.
"static"Manually specify TCP window size.
"dynamic"Vary TCP window size based on available memory and within limits of tcp-window-minimum and tcp-window-maximum.
"auto-tuning"Allow system to auto-tune TCP window size (default).
uncompressed-nest-limitunsigned int32
Maximum nested levels of compression that can be uncompressed and scanned (2 - 100, default = 12).
uncompressed-oversize-limitunsigned int32
Maximum in-memory uncompressed file size that can be scanned.

Table object/pm/config/global/obj/firewall/profile-protocol-options/<profile-protocol-options_name>/http

Attribute ListDescriptions
address-ip-ratingoption
Enable/disable IP based URL rating.
"disable"Disable setting.
"enable"Enable setting.
block-page-status-codeunsigned int32
Code number returned for blocked HTTP pages (non-FortiGuard only) (100 - 599, default = 403).
comfort-amountunsigned int32
Number of bytes to send in each transmission for client comforting (bytes).
comfort-intervalunsigned int32
Interval between successive transmissions of data for client comforting (seconds).
h2coption
Enable/disable h2c HTTP connection upgrade.
"disable"Do not allow h2c HTTP connection upgrades.
"enable"Allow h2c HTTP connection upgrades. h2c tunnels do not support content scan.
inspect-alloption
Enable/disable the inspection of all ports for the protocol.
"disable"Disable setting.
"enable"Enable setting.
optionsflags
One or more options that can be applied to the session.
"oversize"Block oversized file.
"chunkedbypass"Bypass chunked transfer encoded sites.
"clientcomfort"Prevent client timeout.
"servercomfort"Prevent server timeout.
oversize-limitunsigned int32
Maximum in-memory file size that can be scanned (MB).
portsint array
Ports to scan for content (1 - 65535, default = 80).
post-langflags
ID codes for character sets to be used to convert to UTF-8 for banned words and DLP on HTTP posts (maximum of 5 character sets).
"jisx0201"Japanese Industrial Standard 0201.
"jisx0208"Japanese Industrial Standard 0208.
"jisx0212"Japanese Industrial Standard 0212.
"gb2312"Guojia Biaozhun 2312 (simplified Chinese).
"ksc5601-ex"Wansung Korean standard 5601.
"euc-jp"Extended Unicode Japanese.
"sjis"Shift Japanese Industrial Standard.
"iso2022-jp"ISO 2022 Japanese.
"iso2022-jp-1"ISO 2022-1 Japanese.
"iso2022-jp-2"ISO 2022-2 Japanese.
"euc-cn"Extended Unicode Chinese.
"ces-gbk"Extended GB2312 (simplified Chinese).
"hz"Hanzi simplified Chinese.
"ces-big5"Big-5 traditional Chinese.
"euc-kr"Extended Unicode Korean.
"iso2022-jp-3"ISO 2022-3 Japanese.
"iso8859-1"ISO 8859 Part 1 (Western European).
"tis620"Thai Industrial Standard 620.
"cp874"Code Page 874 (Thai).
"cp1252"Code Page 1252 (Western European Latin).
"cp1251"Code Page 1251 (Cyrillic).
proxy-after-tcp-handshakeoption
Proxy traffic after the TCP 3-way handshake has been established (not before).
"disable"Disable setting.
"enable"Enable setting.
range-blockoption
Enable/disable blocking of partial downloads.
"disable"Disable range header blocking (allow partial file downloads)
"enable"Enable range header blocking (treat all partial file downloads as full file download)
retry-countunsigned int32
Number of attempts to retry HTTP connection (0 - 100, default = 0).
scan-bzip2option
Enable/disable scanning of BZip2 compressed files.
"disable"Disable setting.
"enable"Enable setting.
ssl-offloadedoption
SSL decryption and encryption performed by an external device.
"no"SSL decryption and encryption performed by FortiGate when deep-inspection is enabled.
"yes"SSL decryption and encryption performed by an external device.
statusoption
Enable/disable the active status of scanning for this protocol.
"disable"Disable setting.
"enable"Enable setting.
stream-based-uncompressed-limitunsigned int32
Maximum stream-based uncompressed data size that will be scanned in megabytes. Stream-based uncompression used only under certain conditions (unlimited = 0, default = 0).
streaming-content-bypassoption
Enable/disable bypassing of streaming content from buffering.
"disable"Disable bypassing of streaming content from buffering
"enable"Enable bypassing of streaming content from buffering
strip-x-forwarded-foroption
Enable/disable stripping of HTTP X-Forwarded-For header.
"disable"Disable changing of HTTP X-Forwarded-For header.
"enable"Enable replacement of X-Forwarded-For value with 1.1.1.1.
switching-protocolsoption
Bypass from scanning, or block a connection that attempts to switch protocol.
"bypass"Bypass connections when switching protocols.
"block"Block connections when switching protocols.
tcp-window-maximumunsigned int32
Maximum dynamic TCP window size.
tcp-window-minimumunsigned int32
Minimum dynamic TCP window size.
tcp-window-sizeunsigned int32
Set TCP static window size.
tcp-window-typeoption
TCP window type to use for this protocol.
"system"Use system default TCP window size for this protocol.
"static"Manually specify TCP window size.
"dynamic"Vary TCP window size based on available memory and within limits of tcp-window-minimum and tcp-window-maximum.
"auto-tuning"Allow system to auto-tune TCP window size (default).
tunnel-non-httpoption
Configure how to process non-HTTP traffic when a profile configured for HTTP traffic accepts a non-HTTP session. Can occur if an application sends non-HTTP traffic using an HTTP destination port.
"disable"Drop or tear down non-HTTP sessions accepted by the profile.
"enable"Pass non-HTTP sessions through the tunnel without applying protocol optimization, byte-caching, or web caching. TCP protocol optimization is applied.
uncompressed-nest-limitunsigned int32
Maximum nested levels of compression that can be uncompressed and scanned (2 - 100, default = 12).
uncompressed-oversize-limitunsigned int32
Maximum in-memory uncompressed file size that can be scanned.
unknown-content-encodingoption
Configure the action the FortiGate unit will take on unknown content-encoding.
"block"Block HTTP session when unknown content-encoding is detected.
"inspect"Scan HTTP traffic as plain-text when unknown content-encoding is detected.
"bypass"Bypass scan when unknown content-encoding is detected.
unknown-http-versionoption
How to handle HTTP sessions that do not comply with HTTP 0.9, 1.0, or 1.1.
"best-effort"Assume all HTTP sessions comply with HTTP 0.9, 1.0, or 1.1. If a session uses a different HTTP version, it may not parse correctly and the connection may be lost.
"reject"Reject or tear down HTTP sessions that do not use HTTP 0.9, 1.0, or 1.1.
"tunnel"Pass HTTP traffic that does not use HTTP 0.9, 1.0, or 1.1 without applying HTTP protocol optimization, byte-caching, or web caching. TCP protocol optimization is applied.
verify-dns-for-policy-matchingoption
Enable/disable verification of DNS for policy matching.
"disable"Disable setting.
"enable"Enable setting.

"enable"Enable ARP reply.

Comment.

External FQDN address name.

IP address or address range on the external interface that you want to map to an address or address range on the destination network.

Incoming port number range that you want to map to a port number range on the destination network.

Enable to have the VIP send gratuitous ARPs. 0=disabled. Set from 5 up to 8640000 seconds to enable.
http-cookie-ageunsigned int32
Time in minutes that client web browsers should keep a cookie. Default is 60 minutes. 0 = no time limit.
http-cookie-domainstring
Domain that HTTP cookie persistence should apply to.
http-cookie-domain-from-hostoption
Enable/disable use of HTTP cookie domain from host field in HTTP.
"disable"Disable use of HTTP cookie domain from host field in HTTP (use http-cooke-domain setting).
"enable"Enable use of HTTP cookie domain from host field in HTTP.
http-cookie-generationunsigned int32
Generation of HTTP cookie to be accepted. Changing invalidates all existing cookies.
http-cookie-pathstring
Limit HTTP cookie persistence to the specified path.
http-cookie-shareoption
Control sharing of cookies across virtual servers. Use of same-ip means a cookie from one virtual server can be used by another. Disable stops cookie sharing.
"disable"Only allow HTTP cookie to match this virtual server.
"same-ip"Allow HTTP cookie to match any virtual server with same IP.
http-ip-headeroption
For HTTP multiplexing, enable to add the original client IP address in the XForwarded-For HTTP header.
"disable"Disable adding HTTP header.
"enable"Enable adding HTTP header.
http-ip-header-namestring, support meta variable
For HTTP multiplexing, enter a custom HTTPS header name. The original client IP address is added to this header. If empty, X-Forwarded-For is used.
http-multiplexoption
Enable/disable HTTP multiplexing.
"disable"Disable HTTP session multiplexing.
"enable"Enable HTTP session multiplexing.
http-multiplex-max-requestunsigned int32
Maximum number of requests that a multiplex server can handle before disconnecting sessions (default = unlimited).
http-multiplex-ttlunsigned int32
Time-to-live for idle connections to servers.
http-redirectoption
Enable/disable redirection of HTTP to HTTPS.
"disable"Disable redirection of HTTP to HTTPS.
"enable"Enable redirection of HTTP to HTTPS.
http-supported-max-versionoption
Maximum supported HTTP versions. default = HTTP2
"http1"Support HTTP 1.1 and HTTP1.
"http2"Support HTTP2, HTTP 1.1, and HTTP1.
https-cookie-secureoption
Enable/disable verification that inserted HTTPS cookies are secure.
"disable"Do not mark cookie as secure, allow sharing between an HTTP and HTTPS connection.
"enable"Mark inserted cookie as secure, cookie can only be used for HTTPS a connection.

Custom defined ID.

ipv6-mappedportstring, support meta variable

"round-robin"Distribute to server based round robin order.

Maximum length of data in MB before triggering a client rekey (0 = disable).

Allow, deny, or require secure renegotiation of client sessions to comply with RFC 5746.
"deny"Abort any client initiated SSL re-negotiation attempt.
"allow"Allow a SSL client to renegotiate.
"secure"Abort any client initiated SSL re-negotiation attempt that does not use RFC 5746 Secure Renegotiation.

Maximum number of client to FortiGate SSL session states to keep.
ssl-client-session-state-timeoutunsigned int32
Number of minutes to keep client to FortiGate SSL session state.
ssl-client-session-state-typeoption
How to expire SSL sessions for the segment of the SSL connection between the client and the FortiGate.
"disable"Do not keep session states.
"time"Expire session states after this many minutes.
"count"Expire session states when this maximum is reached.
"both"Expire session states based on time or count, whichever occurs first.

Apply SSL offloading between the client and the FortiGate (half) or from the client to the FortiGate and from the FortiGate to the server (full).
"half"Client to FortiGate SSL.
"full"Client to FortiGate and FortiGate to Server SSL.
ssl-pfsoption
Select the cipher suites that can be used for SSL perfect forward secrecy (PFS). Applies to both client and server sessions.
"require"Allow only Diffie-Hellman cipher-suites, so PFS is applied.
"deny"Allow only non-Diffie-Hellman cipher-suites, so PFS is not applied.
"allow"Allow use of any cipher suite so PFS may or may not be used depending on the cipher suite selected.
ssl-send-empty-fragsoption
Enable/disable sending empty fragments to avoid CBC IV attacks (SSL 3.0 & TLS 1.0 only). May need to be disabled for compatibility with older systems.
"disable"Do not send empty fragments.
"enable"Send empty fragments.
ssl-server-algorithmoption
Permitted encryption algorithms for the server side of SSL full mode sessions according to encryption strength.
"high"High encryption. Allow only AES and ChaCha.
"low"Low encryption. Allow AES, ChaCha, 3DES, RC4, and DES.
"medium"Medium encryption. Allow AES, ChaCha, 3DES, and RC4.
"custom"Custom encryption. Use ssl-server-cipher-suites to select the cipher suites that are allowed.
"client"Use the same encryption algorithms for both client and server sessions.
ssl-server-max-versionoption
Highest SSL/TLS version acceptable from a server. Use the client setting by default.
"ssl-3.0"SSL 3.0.
"tls-1.0"TLS 1.0.
"tls-1.1"TLS 1.1.
"tls-1.2"TLS 1.2.
"client"Use same value as client configuration.
"tls-1.3"TLS 1.3.
ssl-server-min-versionoption
Lowest SSL/TLS version acceptable from a server. Use the client setting by default.
"ssl-3.0"SSL 3.0.
"tls-1.0"TLS 1.0.
"tls-1.1"TLS 1.1.
"tls-1.2"TLS 1.2.
"client"Use same value as client configuration.
"tls-1.3"TLS 1.3.
ssl-server-renegotiationoption
Enable/disable secure renegotiation to comply with RFC 5746.
"disable"Disable secure renegotiation.
"enable"Enable secure renegotiation.
ssl-server-session-state-maxunsigned int32
Maximum number of FortiGate to Server SSL session states to keep.
ssl-server-session-state-timeoutunsigned int32
Number of minutes to keep FortiGate to Server SSL session state.
ssl-server-session-state-typeoption
How to expire SSL sessions for the segment of the SSL connection between the server and the FortiGate.
"disable"Do not keep session states.
"time"Expire session states after this many minutes.
"count"Expire session states when this maximum is reached.
"both"Expire session states based on time or count, whichever occurs first.
statusoption
Enable/disable VIP.
"disable"Disable the VIP.
"enable"Enable the VIP.
typeoption
Configure a static NAT, load balance, server load balance, access proxy, DNS translation, or FQDN VIP.
"static-nat"Static NAT.
"load-balance"Load balance.
"server-load-balance"Server load balance.
"dns-translation"DNS translation.
"fqdn"Fully qualified domain name.
"access-proxy"Access proxy.
uuiduuid
Universally Unique Identifier (UUID; automatically assigned but can be manually reset).
weblogic-serveroption
Enable to add an HTTP header to indicate SSL offloading for a WebLogic server.
"disable"Do not add HTTP header indicating SSL offload for WebLogic server.
"enable"Add HTTP header indicating SSL offload for WebLogic server.
websphere-serveroption
Enable to add an HTTP header to indicate SSL offloading for a WebSphere server.
"disable"Do not add HTTP header indicating SSL offload for WebSphere server.
"enable"Add HTTP header indicating SSL offload for WebSphere server.

firewall/vip6 (table)

Configure virtual IP for IPv6.

Supported methods: get (table), get (object), add, set, update, delete, move, clone

Object URL:
Table/pm/config/global/obj/firewall/vip6
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/firewall/vip6
Object/pm/config/global/obj/firewall/vip6/<vip6_name>
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/firewall/vip6/<vip6_name>
Attribute ListDescriptions
add-nat64-routeoption
Enable/disable adding NAT64 route.
"disable"Disable adding NAT64 route.
"enable"Enable adding NAT64 route.
arp-replyoption
Enable to respond to ARP requests for this virtual IP address. Enabled by default.
"disable"Disable ARP reply.
"enable"Enable ARP reply.

Color of icon on the GUI.

Comment.

"enable"Enable use of the lower 32 bits of the external IPv6 address as mapped IPv4 address.

extportport range, support meta variable
Incoming port number range that you want to map to a port number range on the destination network.

Time in minutes that client web browsers should keep a cookie. Default is 60 minutes. 0 = no time limit.

Domain that HTTP cookie persistence should apply to.

"disable"Disable use of HTTP cookie domain from host field in HTTP (use http-cooke-domain setting).
"enable"Enable use of HTTP cookie domain from host field in HTTP.
http-cookie-generationunsigned int32

http-cookie-pathstring
Limit HTTP cookie persistence to the specified path.
http-cookie-shareoption
Control sharing of cookies across virtual servers. Use of same-ip means a cookie from one virtual server can be used by another. Disable stops cookie sharing.
"disable"Only allow HTTP cookie to match this virtual server.
"same-ip"Allow HTTP cookie to match any virtual server with same IP.
http-ip-headeroption
For HTTP multiplexing, enable to add the original client IP address in the XForwarded-For HTTP header.
"disable"Disable adding HTTP header.
"enable"Enable adding HTTP header.
http-ip-header-namestring, support meta variable
For HTTP multiplexing, enter a custom HTTPS header name. The original client IP address is added to this header. If empty, X-Forwarded-For is used.
http-multiplexoption

"disable"Disable HTTP session multiplexing.
"enable"Enable HTTP session multiplexing.
http-redirectoption
Enable/disable redirection of HTTP to HTTPS.
"disable"Disable redirection of HTTP to HTTPS.
"enable"Enable redirection of HTTP to HTTPS.
https-cookie-secureoption
Enable/disable verification that inserted HTTPS cookies are secure.
"disable"Do not mark cookie as secure, allow sharing between an HTTP and HTTPS connection.
"enable"Mark inserted cookie as secure, cookie can only be used for HTTPS a connection.
idunsigned int32
Custom defined ID.
ipv4-mappedipstring, support meta variable
Range of mapped IP addresses. Specify the start IP address followed by a space and the end IP address.
ipv4-mappedportstring, support meta variable
IPv4 port number range on the destination network to which the external port number range is mapped.
ldb-methodoption
Method used to distribute sessions to real servers.
"static"Distribute sessions based on source IP.
"round-robin"Distribute sessions based round robin order.
"weighted"Distribute sessions based on weight.
"least-session"Sends new sessions to the server with the lowest session count.
"least-rtt"Distribute new sessions to the server with lowest Round-Trip-Time.
"first-alive"Distribute sessions to the first server that is alive.
"http-host"Distribute sessions to servers based on host field in HTTP header.
mappedipIPv6 range, support meta variable

mappedportport range, support meta variable
Port number range on the destination network to which the external port number range is mapped.

"enable"Enable Outlook Web Access support.

Enable/disable FFDHE cipher suite for SSL key exchange.
"disable"Do not accept FFDHE groups.
"enable"Accept FFDHE groups.
ssl-algorithmoption
Permitted encryption algorithms for SSL sessions according to encryption strength.
"high"Use AES.
"low"Use AES, 3DES, RC4, or DES.
"medium"Use AES, 3DES, or RC4.
"custom"Use config ssl-cipher-suites to select the cipher suites that are allowed.
ssl-certificatedatasource, refer to vpn certificate local, or dynamic certificate local (maximum 1)
The name of the certificate to use for SSL handshake.
ssl-cipher-suitestable
ssl-client-fallbackoption
Enable/disable support for preventing Downgrade Attacks on client connections (RFC 7507).
"disable"Disable.
"enable"Enable.
ssl-client-rekey-countunsigned int32
Maximum length of data in MB before triggering a client rekey (0 = disable).
ssl-client-renegotiationoption
Allow, deny, or require secure renegotiation of client sessions to comply with RFC 5746.
"deny"Abort any SSL connection that attempts to renegotiate.
"allow"Allow a SSL client to renegotiate.
"secure"Reject any SSL connection that does not offer a RFC 5746 Secure Renegotiation Indication.
ssl-client-session-state-maxunsigned int32
Maximum number of client to FortiGate SSL session states to keep.
ssl-client-session-state-timeoutunsigned int32
Number of minutes to keep client to FortiGate SSL session state.
ssl-client-session-state-typeoption
How to expire SSL sessions for the segment of the SSL connection between the client and the FortiGate.
"disable"Do not keep session states.
"time"Expire session states after this many minutes.
"count"Expire session states when this maximum is reached.
"both"Expire session states based on time or count, whichever occurs first.
ssl-dh-bitsoption
Number of bits to use in the Diffie-Hellman exchange for RSA encryption of SSL sessions.
"768"768-bit Diffie-Hellman prime.
"1024"1024-bit Diffie-Hellman prime.
"1536"1536-bit Diffie-Hellman prime.
"2048"2048-bit Diffie-Hellman prime.
"3072"3072-bit Diffie-Hellman prime.
"4096"4096-bit Diffie-Hellman prime.
ssl-hpkpoption
Enable/disable including HPKP header in response.
"disable"Do not add a HPKP header to each HTTP response.
"enable"Add a HPKP header to each a HTTP response.
"report-only"Add a HPKP Report-Only header to each HTTP response.
ssl-hpkp-ageunsigned int32
Number of minutes the web browser should keep HPKP.
ssl-hpkp-backupdatasource, refer to vpn certificate ca, or vpn certificate local (maximum 1)
Certificate to generate backup HPKP pin from.
ssl-hpkp-include-subdomainsoption
Indicate that HPKP header applies to all subdomains.
"disable"HPKP header does not apply to subdomains.
"enable"HPKP header applies to subdomains.
ssl-hpkp-primarydatasource, refer to vpn certificate ca, or vpn certificate local (maximum 1)
Certificate to generate primary HPKP pin from.
ssl-hpkp-report-uristring
URL to report HPKP violations to.
ssl-hstsoption
Enable/disable including HSTS header in response.
"disable"Do not add a HSTS header to each a HTTP response.
"enable"Add a HSTS header to each HTTP response.
ssl-hsts-ageunsigned int32
Number of seconds the client should honor the HSTS setting.
ssl-hsts-include-subdomainsoption
Indicate that HSTS header applies to all subdomains.
"disable"HSTS header does not apply to subdomains.
"enable"HSTS header applies to subdomains.
ssl-http-location-conversionoption
Enable to replace HTTP with HTTPS in the reply's Location HTTP header field.
"disable"Disable HTTP location conversion.
"enable"Enable HTTP location conversion.
ssl-http-match-hostoption
Enable/disable HTTP host matching for location conversion.
"disable"Do not match HTTP host.
"enable"Match HTTP host in response header.
ssl-max-versionoption
Highest SSL/TLS version acceptable from a client.
"ssl-3.0"SSL 3.0.
"tls-1.0"TLS 1.0.
"tls-1.1"TLS 1.1.
"tls-1.2"TLS 1.2.
"tls-1.3"TLS 1.3.
ssl-min-versionoption
Lowest SSL/TLS version acceptable from a client.
"ssl-3.0"SSL 3.0.
"tls-1.0"TLS 1.0.
"tls-1.1"TLS 1.1.
"tls-1.2"TLS 1.2.
"tls-1.3"TLS 1.3.
ssl-modeoption
Apply SSL offloading between the client and the FortiGate (half) or from the client to the FortiGate and from the FortiGate to the server (full).
"half"Client to FortiGate SSL.
"full"Client to FortiGate and FortiGate to Server SSL.
ssl-pfsoption
Select the cipher suites that can be used for SSL perfect forward secrecy (PFS). Applies to both client and server sessions.
"require"Allow only Diffie-Hellman cipher-suites, so PFS is applied.
"deny"Allow only non-Diffie-Hellman cipher-suites, so PFS is not applied.
"allow"Allow use of any cipher suite so PFS may or may not be used depending on the cipher suite selected.
ssl-send-empty-fragsoption
Enable/disable sending empty fragments to avoid CBC IV attacks (SSL 3.0 & TLS 1.0 only). May need to be disabled for compatibility with older systems.
"disable"Do not send empty fragments.
"enable"Send empty fragments.
ssl-server-algorithmoption
Permitted encryption algorithms for the server side of SSL full mode sessions according to encryption strength.
"high"Use AES.
"low"Use AES, 3DES, RC4, or DES.
"medium"Use AES, 3DES, or RC4.
"custom"Use config ssl-server-cipher-suites to select the cipher suites that are allowed.
"client"Use the same encryption algorithms for client and server sessions.
ssl-server-cipher-suitestable
ssl-server-max-versionoption
Highest SSL/TLS version acceptable from a server. Use the client setting by default.
"ssl-3.0"SSL 3.0.
"tls-1.0"TLS 1.0.
"tls-1.1"TLS 1.1.
"tls-1.2"TLS 1.2.
"client"Use same value as client configuration.
"tls-1.3"TLS 1.3.
ssl-server-min-versionoption
Lowest SSL/TLS version acceptable from a server. Use the client setting by default.
"ssl-3.0"SSL 3.0.
"tls-1.0"TLS 1.0.
"tls-1.1"TLS 1.1.
"tls-1.2"TLS 1.2.
"client"Use same value as client configuration.

firewall/vip6/realservers (table)

Select the real servers that this server load balancing VIP will distribute traffic to.

Supported methods: get (table), get (object), add, set, update, delete, clone

Object URL:
Table/pm/config/global/obj/firewall/vip6/<vip6_name>/realservers
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/firewall/vip6/<vip6_name>/realservers
Object/pm/config/global/obj/firewall/vip6/<vip6_name>/realservers/<realservers_id>
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/firewall/vip6/<vip6_name>/realservers/<realservers_id>
Attribute ListDescriptions
client-ipstring
Only clients in this IP range can connect to this real server.
healthcheckoption
Enable to check the responsiveness of the real server before forwarding traffic.
"disable"Disable per server health check.
"enable"Enable per server health check.
"vip"Use health check defined in VIP.
holddown-intervalunsigned int32
Time in seconds that the health check monitor continues to monitor an unresponsive server that should be active.
http-hoststring
HTTP server domain name in HTTP header.
idsequence, master key
Real server ID.
ipIPv6 address
IP address of the real server.
max-connectionsunsigned int32
Max number of active connections that can directed to the real server. When reached, sessions are sent to other real servers.
monitordatasource, refer to firewall ldb-monitor (maximum 5)
Name of the health check monitor to use when polling to determine a virtual server's connectivity status.
portunsigned int32
Port for communicating with the real server. Required if port forwarding is enabled.
statusoption
Set the status of the real server to active so that it can accept traffic, or on standby or disabled so no traffic is sent.
"active"Server status active.
"standby"Server status standby.
"disable"Server status disable.
translate-hostoption
Enable/disable translation of hostname/IP from virtual server to real server.
"disable"Disable virtual hostname/IP translation.
"enable"Enable virtual hostname/IP translation.
weightunsigned int32
Weight of the real server. If weighted load balancing is enabled, the server with the highest weight gets more connections.

Supported methods: get (table), get (object), add, set, update, delete, clone

Object URL:
Table/pm/config/global/obj/firewall/vipgrp
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/firewall/vipgrp
Object/pm/config/global/obj/firewall/vipgrp/<vipgrp_name>
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/firewall/vipgrp/<vipgrp_name>
Attribute ListDescriptions
colorunsigned int32
Integer value to determine the color of the icon in the GUI (range 1 to 32, default = 0, which sets the value to 1).
commentsstring
Comment.
dynamic_mappingtable
interfacedatasource, refer to system interface, or dynamic interface (maximum 1)
Interface.
memberdatasource, refer to firewall vip (maximum 1024)
Member VIP objects of the group (Separate multiple objects with a space).
namestring, master key

global/ips/sensor/entries (table)

IPS sensor filter.

Supported methods: get (table), get (object), add, set, update, delete, clone

Object URL:
Table/pm/config/global/obj/global/ips/sensor/<sensor_name>/entries
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/global/ips/sensor/<sensor_name>/entries
Object/pm/config/global/obj/global/ips/sensor/<sensor_name>/entries/<entries_id>
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/global/ips/sensor/<sensor_name>/entries/<entries_id>
Attribute ListDescriptions
actionoption
Action taken with traffic in which signatures are detected.
"pass"Pass or allow matching traffic.
"block"Block or drop matching traffic.
"reset"Reset sessions for matching traffic.
"default"Pass or drop matching traffic, depending on the default action of the signature.
applicationstring array
Operating systems to be protected. Use all for every application and other for unlisted application.
cvestring array
List of CVE IDs of the signatures to add to the sensor.
default-actionoption
Signature default action filter.
"block"Selects signatures with default action 'block'.
"pass"Selects signatures with default action 'pass'.
"all"Selects signatures with any default action.
default-statusoption
Signature default status filter.
"disable"Selects signatures disabled by default.
"enable"Selects signatures enabled by default.
"all"Selects signatures with any default status.
exempt-iptable
idsequence, master key
Rule ID in IPS database (0 - 4294967295).
last-modifiedstring array
Filter by signature last modified date. Formats: before <date>, after <date>, between <start-date> <end-date>.
locationstring array
Protect client or server traffic.
logoption
Enable/disable logging of signatures included in filter.
"disable"Disable logging of selected rules.
"enable"Enable logging of selected rules.
log-attack-contextoption
Enable/disable logging of attack context: URL buffer, header buffer, body buffer, packet buffer.
"disable"Disable logging of detailed attack context.
"enable"Enable logging of detailed attack context.
log-packetoption
Enable/disable packet logging. Enable to save the packet that triggers the filter. You can download the packets in pcap format for diagnostic use.
"disable"Disable packet logging of selected rules.
"enable"Enable packet logging of selected rules.
osstring array
Operating systems to be protected. Use all for every operating system and other for unlisted operating systems.
positionoption
"header"
"footer"
protocolstring array
Protocols to be examined. Use all for every protocol and other for unlisted protocols.
quarantineoption
Quarantine method.
"none"Quarantine is disabled.
"attacker"Block all traffic sent from attacker's IP address. The attacker's IP address is also added to the banned user list. The target's address is not affected.
quarantine-expirystring
Duration of quarantine. (Format ###d##h##m, minimum 1m, maximum 364d23h59m, default = 5m). Requires quarantine set to attacker.
quarantine-logoption
Enable/disable quarantine logging.
"disable"Disable quarantine logging.
"enable"Enable quarantine logging.
rate-countunsigned int32
Count of the rate.
rate-durationunsigned int32
Duration (sec) of the rate.
rate-modeoption
Rate limit mode.
"periodical"Allow configured number of packets every rate-duration.
"continuous"Block packets once the rate is reached.
rate-trackoption
Track the packet protocol field.
"none"
"src-ip"Source IP.
"dest-ip"Destination IP.
"dhcp-client-mac"DHCP client.
"dns-domain"DNS domain.
ruledatasource, refer to ips_cus signature
Identifies the predefined or custom IPS signatures to add to the sensor.
severitystring array
Relative severity of the signature, from info to critical. Log messages generated by the signature include the severity.
statusoption
Status of the signatures included in filter. Only those filters with a status to enable are used.
"disable"Disable status of selected rules.
"enable"Enable status of selected rules.
"default"Default.
tagsdatasource, refer to system object-tag
vuln-typeint array
List of signature vulnerability types to filter by.

Maximum percentage of FortiGate memory the antispam cache is allowed to use (1 - 15).
antispam-cache-ttlunsigned int32
Time-to-live for antispam cache entries in seconds (300 - 86400). Lower times reduce the cache size. Higher times may improve performance since the cache will have more entries.

"disable"Disable automatic patch-level firmware upgrade to latest version from FortiGuard.
"enable"Enable automatic patch-level firmware upgrade to latest version from FortiGuard.
auto-firmware-upgrade-dayflags
Allowed day(s) of the week to install an automatic patch-level firmware upgrade from FortiGuard (default is none). Disallow any day of the week to use auto-firmware-upgrade-delay instead, which waits for designated days before installing an automatic patch-level firmware upgrade.
"sunday"Sunday.
"monday"Monday.
"tuesday"Tuesday.
"wednesday"Wednesday.
"thursday"Thursday.
"friday"Friday.
"saturday"Saturday.

Delay of day(s) before installing an automatic patch-level firmware upgrade from FortiGuard (default = 3). Set it 0 to use auto-firmware-upgrade-day instead, which selects allowed day(s) of the week for installing an automatic patch-level firmware upgrade.
auto-firmware-upgrade-end-hourunsigned int32
End time in the designated time window for automatic patch-level firmware upgrade from FortiGuard in 24 hour time (0 ~ 23, default = 4). When the end time is smaller than the start time, the end time is interpreted as the next day. The actual upgrade time is selected randomly within the time window.
auto-firmware-upgrade-start-hourunsigned int32
Start time in the designated time window for automatic patch-level firmware upgrade from FortiGuard in 24 hour time (0 ~ 23, default = 2). The actual upgrade time is selected randomly within the time window.

system/npu/hpe (object)

Host protection engine configuration.

Supported methods: get, set, update

Object URL:
Table object/pm/config/global/obj/system/npu/hpe
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/system/npu/hpe
Attribute ListDescriptions
all-protocolunsigned int32
Maximum packet rate of each host queue except high priority traffic(1K - 32M pps, default = 400K pps), set 0 to disable.
arp-maxunsigned int32
Maximum ARP packet rate (1K - 32M pps, default = 5K pps). Entry is valid when ARP is removed from high-priority traffic.
enable-queue-shaperoption
Enable/Disable NPU host protection engine (HPE) queue shaper.
"disable"Disable NPU HPE per-queue shaping.
"enable"Enable NPU HPE per-queue shaping.
enable-shaperoption
Enable/Disable NPU Host Protection Engine (HPE) for packet type shaper.
"disable"Disable NPU HPE shaping based on packet type.
"enable"Enable NPU HPE shaping based on packet type.
esp-maxunsigned int32
Maximum ESP packet rate (1K - 32M pps, default = 5K pps).
exception-codeunsigned int32
Maximum exception code rate of traffic(1K - 32M pps, default = 1M pps).
fragment-with-sessunsigned int32
Maximum fragment with session rate of traffic(1K - 32M pps, default = 1M pps).
fragment-without-sessionunsigned int32
Maximum fragment without session rate of traffic(1K - 32M pps, default = 1M pps).
high-priorityunsigned int32
Maximum packet rate for high priority traffic packets (1K - 32M pps, default = 400K pps).
icmp-maxunsigned int32
Maximum ICMP packet rate (1K - 32M pps, default = 5K pps).
ip-frag-maxunsigned int32
Maximum fragmented IP packet rate (1K - 32M pps, default = 5K pps).
ip-others-maxunsigned int32
Maximum IP packet rate for other packets (packet types that cannot be set with other options) (1K - 32G pps, default = 5K pps).
l2-others-maxunsigned int32
Maximum L2 packet rate for L2 packets that are not ARP packets (1K - 32M pps, default = 5K pps).
pri-type-maxunsigned int32
Maximum overflow rate of priority type traffic(1K - 32M pps, default = 40K pps). Includes L2: HA, 802.3ad LACP, heartbeats. L3: OSPF. L4_TCP: BGP. L4_UDP: IKE, SLBC, BFD.
queue-shaper-maxunsigned int32
Maximum per queue byte rate of traffic(1K - 32M pps, default = 1M pps).
sctp-maxunsigned int32
Maximum SCTP packet rate (1K - 32M pps, default = 5K pps).
tcp-maxunsigned int32
Maximum TCP packet rate (1K - 32M pps, default = 40K pps).
tcpfin-rst-maxunsigned int32
Maximum TCP carries FIN or RST flags packet rate (1K - 32M pps, default = 40K pps).
tcpsyn-ack-maxunsigned int32
Maximum TCP carries SYN and ACK flags packet rate (1K - 32M pps, default = 40K pps).
tcpsyn-maxunsigned int32
Maximum TCP SYN packet rate (1K - 40M pps, default = 32K pps).
udp-maxunsigned int32
Maximum UDP packet rate (1K - 32M pps, default = 40K pps).

web-proxy/forward-server-group (table)

Configure a forward server group consisting or multiple forward servers. Supports failover and load balancing.

Supported methods: get (table), get (object), add, set, update, delete, clone

Object URL:
Table/pm/config/global/obj/web-proxy/forward-server-group
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/web-proxy/forward-server-group
Object/pm/config/global/obj/web-proxy/forward-server-group/<forward-server-group_name>
/pm/config/adom/<adom_name>/obj/web-proxy/forward-server-group/<forward-server-group_name>
Attribute ListDescriptions
affinityoption
Enable/disable affinity, attaching a source-ip's traffic to the assigned forwarding server until the forward-server-affinity-timeout is reached (under web-proxy global).
"disable"Disable affinity.
"enable"Enable affinity.
group-down-optionoption
Action to take when all of the servers in the forward server group are down: block sessions until at least one server is back up or pass sessions to their destination.
"block"Block sessions until at least one server in the group is back up.
"pass"Pass sessions to their destination bypassing servers in the forward server group.
ldb-methodoption
Load balance method: weighted or least-session.
"weighted"Load balance traffic to forward servers based on assigned weights. Weights are ratios of total number of sessions.
"least-session"Send new sessions to the server with lowest session count.
"active-passive"Send new sessions to the next active server in the list. Servers are selected with highest weight first and then in order as they are configured. Traffic switches back to the first server upon failure recovery.
namestring, master key
Configure a forward server group consisting one or multiple forward servers. Supports failover and load balancing.
server-listtable
